Consider a matrix $A$ and a vector $v$, where:

Matrix $A$:

$$
A = \begin{pmatrix}
a_{11} & a_{12} \\
a_{21} & a_{22}
\end{pmatrix}
$$

Vector $v$:

$$
v = \begin{pmatrix}
v_1 \\
v_2
\end{pmatrix}
$$

The dot product of $A$ and $v$ results in a new vector:

$$
A \cdot v = \begin{pmatrix}
a_{11}v_1 + a_{12}v_2 \\
a_{21}v_1 + a_{22}v_2
\end{pmatrix}
$$

